    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2599</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-19T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 20, 3 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3769. Informed by newspaper correspondent that <persName corresp="#p_ZAFM1"
                        >Zimmermann</persName> told him yesterday that Germany would make no further
                    concessions in submarine war. <persName corresp="#p_ZAFM1"
                    >Zimmermann</persName>, according to <persName corresp="#p_MSS1"
                        >McClure</persName>, read and approved the manifesto given to <persName
                        corresp="#p_MSS1">McClure</persName> and cabled you—my 3754,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d309fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_231">p. 231</ref>.</note>
                    April 16, 4 p. m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
